Regional Rules

Special Rule

These rules are in effect when fighting in the specified region. They affect both armies.

Control Bonus

If you control a region you may use these rules no matter what region you're fighting in. Can you use multiple at once? idk.

MISTY MOUNTAINS

Special Rule

Scenarios always use Dark of Night rules.

Control Bonus

If your faction controls the Misty Mountains, infantry models in your Army gain the Backstabbers Special Rule.

HARAD

Special Rule

Models wearing Heavy Armour and Cavalry suffer –1" Movement.

Control Bonus

If your faction controls Harad, your Heroes gain the Poisoneded Attacks Special Rule.

SOUTHERN GONDOR

Special Rule

All Good models gain Fearless.

Control Bonus

If your faction controls Southern Gondor, all Warrior models in your Army may re-roll failed Courage tests while within 6" of a Hero.

MORDOR

Special Rule

All Evil models may treat their general as a 6" banner.

Control Bonus

If your faction controls Mordor, your Army’s Heroes gain the Terror Special Rule. If already they have Terror, enemies recieve -1 to their Courage test.

THE BROWN LANDS

Special Rule

All models treat open ground as difficult terrain when charging.

Control Bonus

If your faction controls the Brown Lands, your heroes gain the Swift Movement ability.

IRON HILLS

Special Rule

At the end of the Move Phase roll a d6 for each ruin or rocky terrain that has models within 1" of it. On a 1 those models suffer a S2 hit and are knocked prone if they lose a Wound.

Control Bonus

If your faction controls the Iron Hills, infantry models who have not moved this turn gain +1 Defense.

MIRKWOOD

Special Rule

All models without Large Target gain Stalk Unseen.

Control Bonus

If your faction controls Mirkwood, all models in your army gain +1 Sv to a maximum of 2+.

LOTHLORIEN

Special Rule

All Heroes gain 6+ FNP.

Control Bonus

If your faction controls Lothlorien, your Heroes gain Resistance to Magic.

ROHAN

Special Rule

All models gain Horse Lord.

Control Bonus

If your faction controls Rohan, your Heroes Stand Fast range is the entire battlefield.

FANGHORN FOREST

Special Rule

Any model that rolls a natural 1 To Wound in melee suffers one S2 hit.

Control Bonus

If your faction controls Fanghorn, infantry Heroes gain +2" to their movement and may reroll any Climb or Jump tests.

GONDOR

Special Rule

All Good models improve their Courage value by 1.

Control Bonus

If your faction controls Gondor, the range of banners in your Army is increased to 6".

ISENGARD

Special Rule

All Evil models gain +1S when charging.

Control Bonus

If your faction controls Isengard, all Heroes in your Army gain +1 Wound.

ENEDWAITH

Special Rule

Warbands may choose to deploy using the Reinforcements Special Rule starting at 2+.

Control Bonus

If your faction controls Enedwaith, your General may attempt to Disengage if they are engaged when they activate. Roll a 4+, if successful they may back away and then continue their move as normal.

RIVENDELL

Special Rule

During the end phase roll a d6 for each general that has lost a wound. On a 6 they recover 1W.

Control Bonus

If your faction controls Rivendell, your Hero's weapons are all considered to be Elven.

ANGMAR

Special Rule

While fighting in Angmar, all Good models gain Fearful.

Control Bonus

If your faction controls Angmar, your General's weapons gain the Venom trait.

THE SHIRE

Special Rule

While fighting in the Shire, models gain +1S while within 6" of a friendly Hero.

Control Bonus

If your faction controls the Shire, your Heroes gain 1 free Might at the start of the game.

LINDON

Special Rule

While fighting in Lindon, Heroes may reroll Duel rolls of 1.

Control Bonus

If your faction controls Lindon, your Heroes may increase their Fv or Attack value by 1 when outnumbered.
